---
---

<section class="bg-[#1A1816] pt-32 pb-24 px-[10px]">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
    <!-- Section Label -->
    <div class="mb-6" data-animate>
      <p class="font-montserrat text-teal text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase">The Current State</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Heading -->
    <div class="mb-6" data-animate data-delay="1">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-cream text-[clamp(36px,5vw,64px)] leading-[1.08] tracking-[-0.02em] max-w-[800px]">
        Your tools weren't built<br />for <em class="italic text-terracotta">this.</em>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- Subtitle -->
    <div class="max-w-[600px] mb-20" data-animate data-delay="2">
      <p class="font-inter text-cream/50 text-lg leading-[1.6]">
        Compounding workflows are unique. Generic EMRs, fax machines, and spreadsheets can't keep up — and your patients feel it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Pain Point Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6" data-stagger>
      <!-- Pain 1 -->
      <div class="bg-[#22201E] rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cream/5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-fraunces text-terracotta text-xl">01</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-inter text-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
              Protocols live in PDFs and spreadsheets
            </h3>
            <p class="font-inter text-cream/40 text-sm leading-[1.7]">
              Multi-step treatment timelines, dosing adjustments, and compound formulations scattered across documents that no one can search, version, or automate. Every protocol change means manually updating every downstream system.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pain 2 -->
      <div class="bg-[#22201E] rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cream/5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-fraunces text-terracotta text-xl">02</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-inter text-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
              Your EMR doesn't understand compounding
            </h3>
            <p class="font-inter text-cream/40 text-sm leading-[1.7]">
              Generic electronic health records treat compounded prescriptions like an afterthought. No real-time pricing, no pharmacy routing, no compound-specific intake flows. You're forcing a square peg into a round hole.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pain 3 -->
      <div class="bg-[#22201E] rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cream/5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-fraunces text-terracotta text-xl">03</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-inter text-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
              Pharmacy coordination is still manual
            </h3>
            <p class="font-inter text-cream/40 text-sm leading-[1.7]">
              Faxes, phone calls, and status-check emails. Your staff spends 6+ hours a week chasing prescriptions, reconciling invoices, and fielding "where's my order?" calls. That's time stolen from patient care.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pain 4 -->
      <div class="bg-[#22201E] rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cream/5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-fraunces text-terracotta text-xl">04</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-inter text-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
              Patients get fragmented, confusing care
            </h3>
            <p class="font-inter text-cream/40 text-sm leading-[1.7]">
              Different logins for intake, messaging, lab results, and refills. No visibility into their treatment timeline. No automated reminders. They drop off — not because the protocol failed, but because the experience did.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
